# Phase 5 — Expiry Validator

This phase introduces a periodic background worker (the **Expiry Validator**) that verifies active Udemy coupon URLs and marks expired or invalid courses as inactive. This keeps the course catalog fresh, prevents coupon fatigue, and ensures dashboard statistics remain accurate.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Cloudflare / Bot Protection Check**: When verifying Udemy courses, requests are made to `udemy.com`. Udemy utilizes Cloudflare protection. If our server gets blocked (403 Forbidden or 429 Too Many Requests), the validator **must not** mark the course as expired. We will treat 403/429 and network errors as "skipped/unknown" states, preserving the course's active status. Only 404 (Not Found) or 200 (OK) with a parsed price > 0 (or a plain paid message) will trigger expiry. **Please confirm if you have any preferred proxy settings or if the default rotated User-Agent is sufficient.**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Verification Batch Size and Frequency**: By default, the validation job will run every **60 minutes** (configurable via `VALIDATE_INTERVAL_MINUTES` on the backend) and process up to **50 courses per run** (ordered by oldest verified first) to distribute network traffic and prevent hitting rate limits. **Please confirm if these default values are appropriate.**

